title: Baguio chills at 9.2ºC
text:
Baguio chills at 9.2ºC By Helen Flores   
MANILA, Philippines – Baguio City recorded yesterday its lowest temperature so far this year at 9.2 degrees Celsius, the Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical Services Administration (PAGASA) said. 
The temperature was recorded at 5 a.m. 
The weather bureau said it expects colder days ahead in the city as well as in other parts of the country as the northeast monsoon peaks this month. 
PAGASA has also recorded lower temperature readings in other parts of Benguet – 7.4 degrees Celsius at Mount Santo Tomas in Tuba town and six degrees Celsius in Atok. 
Meanwhile, PAGASA said the monsoon will bring today cloudy skies with light rains over the regions of Cagayan Valley, Cordillera, Bicol, Eastern Visayas, Caraga, Davao and the provinces of Aurora, Quezon, Rizal, Misamis Oriental and Bukidnon. 
Metro Manila and the rest of the country will experience partly cloudy to cloudy skies with isolated light rains while the whole archipelago will have moderate to rough seas.
